1
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:40,386
Dmn it!

2
00:03:41,654 --> 00:03:46,114
One, two, three cars...
Absolutely useless.

3
00:04:06,346 --> 00:04:09,042
What's wrong?
What happene driver

4
00:04:09,549 --> 00:04:10,516
Why stop?

5
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:16,088
Sir a Vagrant is lying
unconscious on the ground

6
00:04:16,656 --> 00:04:21,093
He must be a miserable
fellow with no money

7
00:04:21,527 --> 00:04:24,155
Driver, put him in the car

8
00:04:24,864 --> 00:04:29,164
You know it's my duty to
serve humanity.

9
00:04:48,888 --> 00:04:53,450
He is unconscious. It looks
as if he hasn't eaten a thing.

10
00:04:53,893 --> 00:04:55,724
He maybe love sick

11
00:04:56,896 --> 00:04:58,659
He looks like a...

12
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:01,327
Driver fast to the hospital.

13
00:05:06,105 --> 00:05:08,005
O God! save my soul

14
00:05:08,174 --> 00:05:10,870
Doctors want only to operate

15
00:05:12,912 --> 00:05:15,881
So you were faking it,
pretending, eh?

16
00:05:17,583 --> 00:05:21,212
I was completely worn out.
I didn't have train fare

17
00:05:21,754 --> 00:05:23,312
Driver, stop the car!

18
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,883
Blasphemy! Fake!

19
00:05:27,927 --> 00:05:28,894
Get out of the car!

20
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:36,898
As you please.
You were kind a minute ago

21
00:05:37,470 --> 00:05:39,438
Does he suffer from fits?

22
00:05:39,772 --> 00:05:43,572
How dare you! Do you know
who you' re talking to?

23
00:05:43,943 --> 00:05:45,410
Seth Dharmanand

24
00:05:45,812 --> 00:05:48,372
I don't have any sympathy
for your sort.

25
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:54,976
If you want to reform, swear
that you won't lie or cheat

26
00:05:55,822 --> 00:05:57,255
And you' ll speak only
the truth

27
00:05:57,557 --> 00:05:58,922
On the contrary

28
00:05:59,292 --> 00:06:01,726
If you lie, you drive
in a huge car

29
00:06:01,961 --> 00:06:04,191
Soft hands apply eau-de-cologne

30
00:06:04,497 --> 00:06:07,660
Speaking the truth you suffer

31
00:06:08,468 --> 00:06:11,528
Driver, let's go.
HE looks like a crook

32
00:06:11,804 --> 00:06:14,602
Seth Sonachand, if l' m
a crook, a 420....

33
00:06:14,774 --> 00:06:16,332
You' re....

34
00:06:33,826 --> 00:06:35,691
Bombay 420.

35
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:42,566
Let's go, old pal

36
00:07:16,202 --> 00:07:20,002
" My shoes are Japanese.
My trousers are English"

37
00:07:20,206 --> 00:07:24,404
"The cap on my head is Russian
but my heart is lndian"

38
00:07:52,672 --> 00:07:56,506
" I venture into
the big, wide world"

39
00:07:57,076 --> 00:08:00,045
" I walk with my head held high"

40
00:08:05,284 --> 00:08:09,311
" Where does my destination lie,
where will I ever settle?"

41
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:16,728
"The Creator up above us
only knows"

42
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:21,394
" Like true soldiers,
we forge ahead"

43
00:08:52,131 --> 00:08:55,760
" Up and down,
round and round...."

44
00:08:56,135 --> 00:09:03,268
".... flow the eternal
waves of life"

45
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:08,512
" Foolish are those
who sit on the side lines"

46
00:09:09,148 --> 00:09:15,917
" With little care
for their country's fate"

47
00:09:16,822 --> 00:09:20,622
"To forge ahead is like life,
To stopstill is like death"

48
00:09:53,326 --> 00:09:56,955
"There may be many a prince,
many a ruler"

49
00:09:57,196 --> 00:10:04,568
" I m like a prince,
just as spoilt"

50
00:10:06,072 --> 00:10:09,974
" I sit on the mighty throne"

51
00:10:10,376 --> 00:10:17,339
" Whenever I feel in the mood"

52
00:10:18,017 --> 00:10:22,181
"Cry the crowds in mazement:
He looks very fmilar"

53
00:10:22,388 --> 00:10:26,347
"The cap on my head is Russian
but my heart is lndian"

54
00:11:45,171 --> 00:11:46,263
Alms!

55
00:11:47,306 --> 00:11:53,677
Is Bombay filled
with only deaf people?

56
00:11:55,114 --> 00:11:56,274
Only the deaf live here.
- And the blind

57
00:11:56,916 --> 00:12:00,283
People in Bombay
hear the jingle of coins

58
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:02,282
This is Bombay, Bombay

59
00:12:02,521 --> 00:12:06,855
High buildings are made of cement.
People have hearts of stone

60
00:12:07,326 --> 00:12:10,159
Only one thing is sacred,
that's money

61
00:12:10,496 --> 00:12:12,964
Move aside.
It's time for business

62
00:12:15,201 --> 00:12:17,897
Business? You mean work?

63
00:12:18,504 --> 00:12:23,134
That's what l' m looking for.
What can I do to earn my keep?

64
00:12:23,609 --> 00:12:25,770
Do what I do... beg!

65
00:12:26,345 --> 00:12:28,836
Tell me, what kind
of work can I find?

66
00:12:29,348 --> 00:12:33,045
Let me think it over.
Are you educated?

67
00:12:33,352 --> 00:12:37,652
B.A. passed. Look at my
degree. I have it here.

68
00:12:39,525 --> 00:12:40,492
Reliable?

69
00:12:40,893 --> 00:12:44,454
I have a medal for honesty,
a gold medal

70
00:12:45,164 --> 00:12:49,157
Can you work hard?
- 24 hours a day.

71
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:52,494
No jobs here

72
00:12:54,373 --> 00:12:55,601
No jobs?

73
00:12:56,909 --> 00:12:59,878
No work even for
someone educated? Why?

74
00:13:00,212 --> 00:13:03,943
Because this is Bombay.
It's a big city

75
00:13:04,383 --> 00:13:07,614
If you look for work,
you' ll never find it

76
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:12,352
If you live by lying and
cheating there are 420 ways

77
00:13:15,861 --> 00:13:19,695
Thank you, boss.
I've learnt a lot today

78
00:13:26,238 --> 00:13:29,366
How much are these?
- Don't touch

79
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:31,943
8 annas a dozen,
2 annas for 3

80
00:13:33,612 --> 00:13:34,977
What?

81
00:13:36,415 --> 00:13:41,250
Eight annas a dozen
or two annas for three

82
00:13:41,620 --> 00:13:46,057
Two annas for three.
No, three annas for two.

83
00:13:46,425 --> 00:13:50,987
3 annas for 2. It isn't free.
How will I survive.

84
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:54,888
Take them at 2 annas for 3,
or get lost.

85
00:13:55,768 --> 00:13:58,669
Why do you insist?
3 annas for 2

86
00:13:59,438 --> 00:14:02,805
No way! 2 annas for 3

87
00:14:03,576 --> 00:14:04,873
Think it over

88
00:14:07,046 --> 00:14:14,077
Two annas for three
Three annas for two

89
00:14:15,454 --> 00:14:16,887
He must be nuts

90
00:14:18,257 --> 00:14:21,749
Come over here

91
00:14:25,464 --> 00:14:28,228
You want 2 for 3 annas?
Here....

92
00:14:28,467 --> 00:14:29,434
Now we' re talking

93
00:14:32,638 --> 00:14:35,937
Oh yes, the money....
I don't have any

94
00:14:36,809 --> 00:14:39,607
Some other time, but remember
3 annas for two

95
00:14:44,483 --> 00:14:46,041
Here, pay me later

96
00:14:52,024 --> 00:14:53,457
What if I never pay?

97
00:14:54,326 --> 00:14:56,055
I' ll think my son ate them

98
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:04,799
How old is your son?
- He's of your age.

99
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:10,175
Thank you.

100
00:15:12,511 --> 00:15:14,638
You won't misunderstand?

101
00:15:15,648 --> 00:15:19,607
You don't have bananas
but a heart of gold

102
00:15:20,653 --> 00:15:21,950
I' ll pay

103
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:28,150
He really is nuts, so naive

104
00:15:32,531 --> 00:15:33,759
Like a banana?

105
00:15:38,537 --> 00:15:40,630
Don't throw the skin anywhere

106
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:43,299
Some don't care about others

107
00:15:44,176 --> 00:15:48,806
They peel the banana and
they fling.....

108
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:49,915
it anywhere

109
00:16:00,259 --> 00:16:04,753
Uncouth people eating bananas
and throwing the peal anywhere.

110
00:16:26,752 --> 00:16:29,880
What nonsense!
- This is Bombay

111
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:33,155
Everyone laughs at others

112
00:16:33,459 --> 00:16:37,156
When they slip themselves,
they stop laughing

113
00:16:45,204 --> 00:16:46,967
You' re right, brother

114
00:16:49,608 --> 00:16:50,575
Tell me

115
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:54,270
Is there a pawn shop
in the area?

116
00:16:55,614 --> 00:16:57,844
It's over there

117
00:16:58,350 --> 00:17:01,410
Everything is sold and bought

118
00:17:03,622 --> 00:17:06,250
Vidya, you've come
to collect your earrings?

119
00:17:06,759 --> 00:17:10,456
No, I've come to sell
these bangles as well

120
00:17:11,096 --> 00:17:13,792
The school isn't running well?

121
00:17:15,434 --> 00:17:17,868
Get the money from the cashier.

122
00:17:18,637 --> 00:17:21,765
Keep them. When you
have the money, return it

123
00:17:25,477 --> 00:17:28,776
Who knows? Maybe I won't
ever see that day

124
00:17:29,081 --> 00:17:31,276
Why talk like that?
It saddens me

125
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:37,511
One day, a prince will come
into your life

126
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:43,791
He' ll be handsome and rich.
When he sees you, he' ll be yours

127
00:17:43,996 --> 00:17:45,293
And then he' ll marry you

128
00:17:45,664 --> 00:17:49,031
He' ll shower you
with jewellery.

129
00:17:49,668 --> 00:17:53,160
Then you can return
all you owe me in one go

130
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:57,368
Take the money. Greet your
father. I' ll visit on Friday

131
00:17:57,676 --> 00:17:58,973
What is it?

132
00:18:02,681 --> 00:18:04,046
What can I show you?

133
00:18:05,851 --> 00:18:08,376
Nothing to buy,
something to sell

134
00:18:08,687 --> 00:18:11,315
That's exactly
what they all say

135
00:18:11,690 --> 00:18:15,524
What is it?
- Honesty

136
00:18:15,961 --> 00:18:17,394
What?

137
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,526
I' ll sell honesty

138
00:18:22,701 --> 00:18:23,929
Here it is

139
00:18:25,871 --> 00:18:29,830
Rashtriya Orphanage
Honesty Medal

140
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:33,411
How much will I get?

141
00:18:34,546 --> 00:18:37,344
If honesty is sold,
what's left in life?

142
00:18:37,716 --> 00:18:40,685
Did you say something?
- No, nothing

143
00:18:41,553 --> 00:18:43,521
Uncle, l' ll be off

144
00:18:50,529 --> 00:18:54,158
You pawning it or selling it?

145
00:18:57,736 --> 00:18:59,363
I thought I'd sell it

146
00:19:01,306 --> 00:19:06,209
It's always been with me.
I' ll sell it and be done with it

147
00:19:07,346 --> 00:19:08,540
Maybe someday....

148
00:19:10,749 --> 00:19:11,977
Forty rupees

149
00:19:12,751 --> 00:19:14,616
To get it back, pay 50

150
00:19:17,756 --> 00:19:21,453
Now you watch! With these
40 rupees, l' ll buy Bombay

151
00:19:23,562 --> 00:19:27,896
That's what everyone thinks.
But no one can buy Bombay.

152
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:29,397
Bombay buys everyone

153
00:19:29,635 --> 00:19:32,604
Everyone ends up right here

154
00:19:54,293 --> 00:19:55,760
I've got money

155
00:20:06,805 --> 00:20:08,033
Here's a 2 rupees

156
00:20:11,376 --> 00:20:12,638
Show!

157
00:20:14,980 --> 00:20:17,778
I' ll pay 5 rupees.
I have it here.

158
00:20:22,387 --> 00:20:24,787
My money!

159
00:20:25,190 --> 00:20:26,487
Who's taken it?

160
00:20:26,658 --> 00:20:29,786
You scoundrels!
420's! Crooks!

161
00:20:36,835 --> 00:20:41,329
Thieves! You play cards
and you rob decent people

162
00:20:41,540 --> 00:20:43,269
Aren't you ashmed?

163
00:21:26,718 --> 00:21:28,845
Where do you think
you' re going?

164
00:21:29,688 --> 00:21:31,315
Can't you see this is reserved?

165
00:21:31,757 --> 00:21:32,724
Go away!

166
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:36,450
Would you mind
if I slept here tonight?

167
00:21:40,699 --> 00:21:41,666
Pay a shirt

168
00:21:42,067 --> 00:21:45,036
No shirt. I've a Russian
cap instead

169
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:49,400
Don't you get it? A deposit!
I mean money, cash

170
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:52,877
I paid 3 rupees.
pay half and stay

171
00:21:54,913 --> 00:21:55,880
Rs. 1.50?

172
00:21:57,549 --> 00:21:59,540
That much just to sleep here?

173
00:21:59,818 --> 00:22:00,876
Yes, 1.50

174
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:05,479
What do you think? Even a dog
has to pay to sleep here

175
00:22:05,924 --> 00:22:09,155
This Footpath is specially
very soft

176
00:22:09,394 --> 00:22:11,885
Next door to Seth Dharmanand

177
00:22:16,935 --> 00:22:20,098
When he sits to dinner
and the air blows here....

178
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:22,239
Ah, the aroma!

179
00:22:24,076 --> 00:22:26,237
I don't have money even
to buy poison.

180
00:22:26,678 --> 00:22:28,578
Let me sleep here tonight.

181
00:22:28,947 --> 00:22:30,312
You are not home.

182
00:22:30,749 --> 00:22:31,909
Why involve my fmily

183
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:35,912
Well, what will you do
if I sleep here?

184
00:22:40,959 --> 00:22:43,587
What are you doing?

185
00:22:45,163 --> 00:22:47,654
Picking on him as he's alone

186
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:53,262
May I ask if this pavement
is yours

187
00:22:57,042 --> 00:23:00,739
No one owns this foothpath,
this is side-walk

188
00:23:00,979 --> 00:23:02,947
It belongs to the State

189
00:23:03,248 --> 00:23:09,551
Hello, lady banana seller
- How come you' re here?

190
00:23:10,188 --> 00:23:13,157
What's going on?
- Nothing, really..

191
00:23:13,558 --> 00:23:16,356
I was walking and felt
tired so I sat down

192
00:23:16,628 --> 00:23:19,256
These brothers were
looking after me.

193
00:23:20,465 --> 00:23:25,232
Were they beating you?
What were they up to?

194
00:23:25,570 --> 00:23:28,971
Bravo! Hitting the poor boy.

195
00:23:36,081 --> 00:23:38,982
Did they hurt you?

196
00:23:41,019 --> 00:23:45,786
Where do you live?
Where do you sleep?

197
00:23:48,493 --> 00:23:52,520
Nowhere. Where do people
who live nowhere, live?

198
00:23:54,032 --> 00:23:57,490
Right here. Stay with us
on the government's pavement.

199
00:24:01,373 --> 00:24:04,467
Listen everyone,
regard him as our son

200
00:24:05,043 --> 00:24:08,843
Take good care of him.
Treat him well. Help him.

201
00:24:09,548 --> 00:24:11,175
You' ll stay here

202
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:14,178
This foothpath is our domain

203
00:24:28,066 --> 00:24:29,363
Sit comfortably

204
00:24:29,568 --> 00:24:31,536
Bring tea and snacks

205
00:24:31,670 --> 00:24:35,367
Don't forget the chillies.
Forgive me if I hurt you.

206
00:24:38,343 --> 00:24:41,506
Don't worry. Ganga Ma's
children are like brothers

207
00:24:42,080 --> 00:24:45,538
I' m like your brother,
what's your nme?

208
00:24:49,554 --> 00:24:52,921
I told you all once,
our day would come

209
00:24:53,091 --> 00:24:54,319
Our Raj is here

210
00:24:59,498 --> 00:25:01,398
What do you do for a living?

211
00:25:04,269 --> 00:25:07,329
I' m looking for work.
What a job that is!

212
00:25:09,608 --> 00:25:12,805
You seem to be new here,
that's why you look for work

213
00:25:13,245 --> 00:25:15,873
Or else you'd have fun
like us

214
00:25:16,781 --> 00:25:18,578
What do you do?

215
00:25:20,118 --> 00:25:21,415
Jobless!

216
00:25:29,194 --> 00:25:33,563
Our stories can be told
in a single word : "jobless".

217
00:25:34,299 --> 00:25:38,759
Tell us your story.
Where are you from?

218
00:25:39,704 --> 00:25:43,265
If we' re to be as one,
tell your story.

219
00:25:43,608 --> 00:25:46,702
Tell us something exciting,
I feel sad today

220
00:26:29,187 --> 00:26:31,314
"O Gently people,
hear this story"

221
00:26:36,027 --> 00:26:42,728
" A simple story with no frills,
aimed to give many thrills"

222
00:27:04,089 --> 00:27:06,057
" I was once a boy
of a poor fmily...."

223
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:10,787
".... who inherited
his mother's destiny"

224
00:27:17,569 --> 00:27:22,006
"Grief and suffering
" Pain and breath did blend"

225
00:27:45,897 --> 00:27:47,797
" Alas! With a face such as mine"

226
00:27:49,934 --> 00:27:52,425
" A thief and l
look one of a kind'

227
00:27:59,177 --> 00:28:03,511
"On the street, one day,
for no rhyme or reason"

228
00:28:03,682 --> 00:28:05,707
" An officer took me away"

229
00:28:27,038 --> 00:28:29,063
" An Officer
Peered over his spectacles"

230
00:28:31,576 --> 00:28:38,277
" He looked me over
barring no obstacles"

231
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:42,543
"Said he : "Can you see no more" "

232
00:28:42,721 --> 00:28:44,951
" He' s the warden' s brother-in-law"

233
00:29:11,816 --> 00:29:18,517
" l' m still bound by misery
l' m happy but not in ecstasy"

234
00:29:25,263 --> 00:29:29,199
" My destination lies before me.
My feet are tied for all to see"

235
00:29:29,367 --> 00:29:31,494
" Rich folk hinder the fun"

236
00:29:59,063 --> 00:30:01,031
" Heed me but tell none"

237
00:30:03,201 --> 00:30:05,567
" Don't walk with head down"

238
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:16,369
" Don't sing without rhyme.
Don't shout without reason"

239
00:30:16,581 --> 00:30:18,981
"Or you will end up in prison!"

240
00:32:06,357 --> 00:32:08,052
Why were you sleeping here?
- Sir?

241
00:32:09,527 --> 00:32:13,327
The problem is,
I had a row with my wife

242
00:32:13,531 --> 00:32:15,499
She threw me out of the house

243
00:32:15,867 --> 00:32:18,335
You know the women
of today are like men

244
00:32:21,539 --> 00:32:22,767
Get lost.

245
00:32:23,074 --> 00:32:25,702
Is this a place to sleep?
Get lost.

246
00:32:30,815 --> 00:32:36,776
Go on! He must be a newcomer.
He's nuts

247
00:32:49,033 --> 00:32:50,728
What are you doing?

248
00:32:51,402 --> 00:32:53,199
Can't you see?

249
00:32:55,573 --> 00:32:56,870
Why are you doing that?

250
00:33:00,912 --> 00:33:04,279
To see this wretched world....

251
00:33:04,449 --> 00:33:05,939
You have to look at it
upside down

252
00:33:06,584 --> 00:33:09,951
All the leaders of the
country do the sme thing

253
00:33:10,254 --> 00:33:11,551
Then, they see it right

254
00:33:14,125 --> 00:33:16,821
Behave yourself
or l' ll straighten you out

255
