will build us homes

510
00:56:00,123 --> 00:56:01,090
Fine homes

511
00:56:02,158 --> 00:56:05,457
It's possible that
like us will have homes

512
00:56:07,430 --> 00:56:10,524
How shall we pay the rent?

513
00:56:11,568 --> 00:56:14,264
For anything one must have a job

514
00:56:14,604 --> 00:56:15,935
A worthwhile job

515
00:56:16,139 --> 00:56:16,935
Listen!

516
00:56:17,173 --> 00:56:18,606
I was working in a laundry

517
00:56:18,808 --> 00:56:21,675
I was paid 45 rupees a month

518
00:56:21,978 --> 00:56:24,742
The owner cut 20 rupees
because I burnt a cloth

519
00:56:24,981 --> 00:56:25,948
Is that fair?

520
00:56:26,116 --> 00:56:27,208
I spit at honest work

521
00:56:28,585 --> 00:56:32,749
You left the job? But why?

522
00:56:32,989 --> 00:56:34,354
I was fed up. I quit

523
00:56:35,992 --> 00:56:38,825
You won't go back?

524
00:56:39,229 --> 00:56:40,958
I' ll find work

525
00:56:42,599 --> 00:56:43,827
Where did you work?

526
00:56:44,167 --> 00:56:45,794
At the JAl BHARAT Laundry

527
00:57:03,553 --> 00:57:04,850
Have you worked in one?

528
00:57:06,022 --> 00:57:10,516
I worked at the Sunlight Soap
factory, I mean laundry

529
00:57:11,594 --> 00:57:14,324
I can't tell you
how well I wash clothes

530
00:57:15,832 --> 00:57:16,799
Do you have an iron?

531
00:57:19,035 --> 00:57:24,871
A wife? How can l? I don't
have a job or a house.

532
00:57:25,208 --> 00:57:27,506
I didn't say a `Wife',
but an iron!

533
00:57:30,580 --> 00:57:35,347
I thought you said a `Wife'.
About the ironing, sir....

534
00:57:35,652 --> 00:57:37,017
I' m from a line of washermen

535
00:57:37,720 --> 00:57:40,553
You look a clown.
Can you work hard?

536
00:57:41,658 --> 00:57:42,625
Yes, Sir!

537
00:57:43,059 --> 00:57:45,493
Will you be honest?
- Yes, Sir.

538
00:57:46,529 --> 00:57:48,019
You've got the job.

539
00:57:54,671 --> 00:57:57,196
Thank you sir, thank you.

540
00:57:58,074 --> 00:58:01,043
You' ll be paid 45 rupees.
Start now.

541
00:58:17,227 --> 00:58:20,196
Rm, how is it spelt?
-R....A....M

542
00:58:21,331 --> 00:58:24,459
Raj, how is it spelt?
-R....A....J

543
00:58:34,744 --> 00:58:35,711
Once, again, children!

544
00:58:43,920 --> 00:58:46,889
I m sorry,
I can't understand you

545
00:58:49,259 --> 00:58:55,289
Why do you dress like this
and act like a clown?

546
00:59:14,017 --> 00:59:16,850
Who is it?
Oh, it's you!

547
00:59:18,154 --> 00:59:21,385
How are you?
I cme to give you this

548
00:59:21,824 --> 00:59:24,987
Why did you take the trouble?
-lt was my duty.

549
00:59:25,962 --> 00:59:27,930
How is Panditji?
How are you?

550
00:59:28,431 --> 00:59:30,626
I've some news.
I have bought a laundry

551
00:59:32,869 --> 00:59:34,302
It's in Parsi bazaar

552
00:59:34,771 --> 00:59:35,999
To get there walk....

553
00:59:36,172 --> 00:59:41,303
....just left of Kharsi Parsi
If you feel like it, come visit

554
00:59:41,578 --> 00:59:42,806
I got a new suit

555
00:59:45,181 --> 00:59:48,150
I couldn't visit earlier,
l' m so busy at work

556
00:59:48,851 --> 00:59:50,876
At last, I found
a spare moment today

557
00:59:56,593 --> 01:00:02,327
I m very busy.
It's late. I' ll go now.

558
01:01:07,597 --> 01:01:09,064
I thought I just saw you
putting on a coat

559
01:01:09,265 --> 01:01:10,562
Fooled by appearance

560
01:01:11,401 --> 01:01:15,030
Clothes are tailored for human
beings and not vice-verse

561
01:01:15,271 --> 01:01:16,238
I don't understand

562
01:01:18,107 --> 01:01:19,074
The dress....

563
01:01:20,276 --> 01:01:22,244
The man. What do you say?

564
01:01:26,282 --> 01:01:29,251
I cme to see how
your laundry is doing

565
01:01:29,552 --> 01:01:30,849
Very well

566
01:01:31,087 --> 01:01:32,384
1 5 or 20 people work here

567
01:01:33,156 --> 01:01:35,590
I' m the boss
We eat and drink well

568
01:01:36,726 --> 01:01:40,526
I didn't wear the suit.
It may get spoilt in the rain.

569
01:01:41,297 --> 01:01:43,162
What will you have?

570
01:01:44,634 --> 01:01:46,067
Where will you have tea?

571
01:01:47,470 --> 01:01:49,597
At the Taj or at the Greens?

572
01:01:51,174 --> 01:01:52,266
They' re too far away

573
01:01:52,475 --> 01:01:53,908
I' m very tired as well

574
01:01:54,977 --> 01:01:59,073
The local foothpath Palace Hotel.
It isn't very far

575
01:02:11,894 --> 01:02:15,022
Here's the foothpath restaurant.
Limited furniture

576
01:02:15,998 --> 01:02:18,296
Make yourself comfortable,
l' ll be back

577
01:02:20,002 --> 01:02:24,302
Two special teas, with milk and
sugar.... double the tea

578
01:02:25,007 --> 01:02:26,474
And the unpaid bills?

579
01:02:26,676 --> 01:02:31,170
You don't seem to see
the delicate predicment l' m in

580
01:02:32,348 --> 01:02:35,579
Please wait until I get paid.
Look who's here with me.

581
01:02:36,352 --> 01:02:37,649
Why should I care?

582
01:02:38,221 --> 01:02:40,121
You already owe me 6 rupees
10 annas

583
01:02:40,423 --> 01:02:43,051
Please understand

584
01:02:46,095 --> 01:02:49,826
Let me have some tea,
my honour's at stake

585
01:02:51,367 --> 01:02:52,857
At least, pay for today's order

586
01:03:00,143 --> 01:03:04,204
Taste Uncle's tea,
you won't go else where

587
01:03:15,525 --> 01:03:19,552
Have you got two annas?
- You mean some change?

588
01:03:19,862 --> 01:03:24,162
I've no change for a hundred
and uncle never has any either

589
01:03:24,534 --> 01:03:25,501
Right, Uncle?

590
01:03:59,168 --> 01:04:00,533
Can I ask something?

591
01:04:04,440 --> 01:04:07,136
If two decent young people
fall in love....

592
01:04:08,044 --> 01:04:09,409
They should marry, right?

593
01:04:12,448 --> 01:04:15,884
When they marry,
they must have children

594
01:04:17,620 --> 01:04:23,923
They will need a home and
clothes to dress the children

595
01:04:25,061 --> 01:04:27,586
Later, the children must
be sent to school

596
01:04:31,467 --> 01:04:34,231
I earn only rupees 45
at the laundry

597
01:04:35,037 --> 01:04:39,064
How can I drem of a marriage
life on 45 rupees, tell me?

598
01:04:41,344 --> 01:04:45,974
A man alone cannot do it, but
if both of them work together

599
01:04:47,650 --> 01:04:51,711
You mean.... Vidya, you and l?

600
01:05:15,511 --> 01:05:18,139
I' ll come to talk
to your father tomorrow

601
01:06:26,148 --> 01:06:29,447
" We' re in love,
We know it's passion"

602
01:06:29,785 --> 01:06:32,754
" Why are our hearts
filled with apprehension?"

603
01:06:40,930 --> 01:06:43,831
" My heart warns me
the path ahead isn't easy"

604
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:47,697
" Little do we know where we go
Our destination is hazy."

605
01:07:31,714 --> 01:07:38,210
" Assure me no change
will enter our love's rhyme."

606
01:07:38,988 --> 01:07:45,621
" Assure me you' ll
not change with passing time"

607
01:07:46,228 --> 01:07:49,629
"One day,
if you' re no longer mine"

608
01:07:49,999 --> 01:07:52,900
"The moon will no longer shine"

609
01:08:45,321 --> 01:08:51,692
" Each night will be
filled with our story"

610
01:08:52,161 --> 01:08:58,794
"The youth of tomorrow
will sing our melody"

611
01:08:59,535 --> 01:09:02,834
" Neither you nor I will remain"

612
01:09:03,272 --> 01:09:06,173
" But the tokens
of our love will reign."

613
01:10:14,810 --> 01:10:16,107
Constable! It's you.

614
01:10:18,747 --> 01:10:21,978
Is your wife still angry?

615
01:10:23,152 --> 01:10:24,779
Wife? The iron!

616
01:10:25,955 --> 01:10:27,445
Oh Lord! Fire! Water!

617
01:10:45,074 --> 01:10:46,473
Fetch some water!

618
01:10:46,709 --> 01:10:48,677
Hurry up, bring the water!

619
01:10:58,354 --> 01:10:59,821
What's going on?
What's the matter?

620
01:11:01,690 --> 01:11:02,156
What's this nonsense?

621
01:11:02,458 --> 01:11:04,085
Stop this nonsense!

622
01:11:40,896 --> 01:11:41,863
Who did it?

623
01:11:43,899 --> 01:11:44,866
Whose iron is this?

624
01:11:47,236 --> 01:11:51,536
It was my mistake,
I left my iron here

625
01:11:51,907 --> 01:11:52,874
Well done!

626
01:11:53,609 --> 01:11:56,407
You spoke the truth,
you will be fined

627
01:11:56,712 --> 01:12:00,876
You' ll work tomorrow as well.
- But tomorrow's Sunday!

628
01:12:01,183 --> 01:12:03,208
I must see someone.
- Shut Up!

629
01:13:38,013 --> 01:13:39,310
Three jacks

630
01:13:42,017 --> 01:13:43,314
Three queens

631
01:13:44,820 --> 01:13:47,789
What about you? Three kings

632
01:13:49,291 --> 01:13:50,485
Let me see

633
01:13:50,793 --> 01:13:52,260
Three aces

634
01:14:01,904 --> 01:14:03,201
Excellent!

635
01:14:07,109 --> 01:14:09,839
Excuse me Madm,
here are the clothes

636
01:14:12,047 --> 01:14:13,810
I' m only here
delivering clothes

637
01:14:14,116 --> 01:14:15,083
Must be John's

638
01:14:16,051 --> 01:14:17,678
That's right

639
01:14:18,053 --> 01:14:23,013
I' m from Sunlight Laundry,
I mean the Bharat Laundry

640
01:14:24,259 --> 01:14:26,352
Sit down

641
01:14:28,630 --> 01:14:30,359
It was my mistake....
Please forgive me

642
01:14:32,067 --> 01:14:34,900
Don't report it
or else l' ll be fired

643
01:14:35,270 --> 01:14:36,430
Sit down!

644
01:14:41,076 --> 01:14:43,374
Madm Please,
I don't know anything

645
01:14:44,746 --> 01:14:49,046
Don't misunderstand me,
I was only passing time

646
01:14:50,085 --> 01:14:51,052
Deal now.

647
01:14:59,461 --> 01:15:01,190
Look at your cards, 3 aces

648
01:15:01,430 --> 01:15:04,058
It's the truth,
l' m not a crook, l' m not a 420

649
01:15:20,782 --> 01:15:22,010
I'd better be off

650
01:15:30,993 --> 01:15:34,087
I' m not a cardsharp.
Don't report me to the police.

651
01:15:34,329 --> 01:15:36,957
I can't afford to lose my job.

652
01:15:37,466 --> 01:15:40,094
Here's the bill. Please sign it.

653
01:15:42,804 --> 01:15:45,796
Sit down. I' ll be back

654
01:15:55,150 --> 01:15:56,117
Come here, Johnny

655
01:15:56,485 --> 01:15:59,852
Meet a true magician

656
01:16:00,622 --> 01:16:02,283
He deals and three aces appear

657
01:16:05,861 --> 01:16:06,987
Always drinking!

658
01:16:07,296 --> 01:16:08,456
I wish you were alert

659
01:16:10,165 --> 01:16:11,462
We've to rush to the party

